---
title: "The Process — Slade Networks"
description: "Clear, step-by-step network installation process for homes and small businesses in the Finger Lakes and surrounding areas in upstate NY."
navActive: process
---
{% extends "base.njk" %}

{% block pageStyles %}
  <style>
    .ctaSection { padding: 0 0 72px }

    @media(max-width:700px) {
      .benefitList { grid-template-columns: 1fr }
    }
  </style>
{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
  <main>
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="heroBadge">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="9 11 12 14 22 4"/><path d="M21 12v7a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V5a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h11"/></svg>
          Clear from start to finish
        </div>
        <h1>How it works</h1>
        <p class="subtext">
          No surprises, no guesswork. Here's exactly what to expect — from the first conversation to a working system, and beyond.
        </p>

        <div class="steps reveal-stagger" aria-label="Project steps">
          <article class="step">
            <div class="stepHeader">
              <div class="number" aria-hidden="true">1</div>
              <h2>Free on-site consultation</h2>
            </div>
            <p>
              We come to you. We walk through the space, talk through what's not working or what you want to add — better Wi-Fi, cameras, phones, or all three — and map the layout so coverage can be planned before anything is installed. You won't be quoted off a phone call or a floor plan.
            </p>
          </article>

          <article class="step">
            <div class="stepHeader">
              <div class="number" aria-hidden="true">2</div>
              <h2>Custom plan and written quote</h2>
            </div>
            <p>
              You'll get a clear plan showing where everything goes, what hardware is needed, and exactly what it costs — all in writing before any work begins. No vague estimates, no surprise add-ons at the end.
            </p>
          </article>

          <article class="step">
            <div class="stepHeader">
              <div class="number" aria-hidden="true">3</div>
              <h2>Installation</h2>
            </div>
            <p>
              Equipment goes in cleanly — cables routed neatly, gear mounted properly, everything labeled so it's easy to work on later. The goal is a finished system that looks like a professional job, not a pile of gear shoved in a closet.
            </p>
          </article>

          <article class="step">
            <div class="stepHeader">
              <div class="number" aria-hidden="true">4</div>
              <h2>Testing and handoff</h2>
            </div>
            <p>
              Before we leave, everything is verified. Wi-Fi coverage is spot-checked, cameras are confirmed recording and playing back, and calling is tested end-to-end. You get a walkthrough of how everything works and your own admin access — nothing is locked away or hidden.
            </p>
          </article>

          <article class="step featured">
            <div class="stepBadge">Recommended add-on</div>
            <div class="stepHeader">
              <div class="number" aria-hidden="true">5</div>
              <h2>Ongoing Support Plan</h2>
            </div>
            <p>
              Most problems that come up after an install don't need a site visit — they need someone who knows the system and can fix it remotely, fast. With an ongoing support plan, we monitor your network, handle firmware updates before they cause issues, and troubleshoot problems remotely so you're not dealing with it yourself.
            </p>
            <p>
              It's the difference between owning a system and having to manage it yourself, versus having someone watch over it for you. Especially useful for businesses where downtime costs real money.
            </p>
            <ul class="benefitList" aria-label="Support plan benefits">
              <li>Remote monitoring</li>
              <li>Priority response</li>
              <li>Firmware updates handled for you</li>
              <li>Remote troubleshooting</li>
              <li>Most issues fixed without a site visit</li>
              <li>One point of contact for anything network</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="ctaSection reveal">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="ctaInner">
          <div>
            <h2>Ready to get started?</h2>
            <p>Book a free consultation and we'll put together the right plan for your space.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="ctaButtons">
            <a class="btn primary" href="/contact/">Request a free consultation</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
{% endblock %}
